subsection.p:
Another way of convincing yourself that y is false is to convince yourself that 
eg y is true:
 egin{split} 
eg ((\exists b)_{\mathbb{R}^+} (( orall a)_{\mathbb{R}^+}(a b = 1))) &\Leftrightarrow ( orall b)_{\mathbb{R}^+}
eg (( orall a)_{\mathbb{R}^+}(a b = 1))\ & \Leftrightarrow ( orall b)_{\mathbb{R}^+} ((\exists a)_{\mathbb{R}^+}(a b 
eq 1)) \end{split}
In words, for each value of b, there is a value for a that makes a b 
eq 1. One such value is a= rac{1}{b}+1. Therefore, 
eg y is true.
